                                PrintFiles 

        This program enables you to print files from the Workbench, without
having to open application program that created the files. You can print
more than one file at a time by using multiple selection or drag selection.

        To use the program, first select the icon of the first file you
wish to print, then if necessary press shift and select the icon of the
other files you wish to print. You can also select multiple files by
dragging a box around a box around the files you wish to print. Once you've
selected all the files you want, hold down shift and double click on the
PrintFiles icon. The files will now be printed out on your printer. If you
want to add a form feed between each file, that is if you want each file to
start on a page, you can add the Tool Type FLAGS=formfeed in the icon's
Information window.


        Workbench 3 PrintFiles work exactly the same under Workbench 3,
except that the form feed Tool Type is specified this way:

                        FORMFEED=true.



